1
00:00:05,605 --> 00:00:08,407
They don’t say
like the Indian man said to me,

2
00:00:08,407 --> 00:00:11,013
(I told Prabhupād
when he asked me
 

3
00:00:11,013 --> 00:00:14,228
about my Indian preaching)
and the Indian man said,

4
00:00:14,228 --> 00:00:16,078
(we would come to preach,
and he said)

5
00:00:16,078 --> 00:00:19,138
“Oh, I know what is Kṛṣṇa.”

6
00:00:19,138 --> 00:00:22,586
And Prabhupād said,
“That is their disease.”

7
00:00:22,646 --> 00:00:26,115
[Erotic Potential in Unalloyed Devotion]

8
00:00:26,115 --> 00:00:29,795
Beyond the grasp
of the mind and the intellect,

9
00:00:29,795 --> 00:00:30,925
this is important.

10
00:00:30,925 --> 00:00:35,475
ataḥ śrī-kṛṣṇa-nāmādi
na bhaved grāhyam indriyaiḥ
[Cc: 2.17.136]

11
00:00:35,475 --> 00:00:37,847
At the same time 
we are saying

12
00:00:37,847 --> 00:00:41,623
the name, form, qualities
pastimes of Kṛṣṇa

13
00:00:41,623 --> 00:00:46,277
are beyond the grasp
of the mind and intellect.

14
00:00:46,814 --> 00:00:54,145
The senses beyond what can be seen,
heard, tasted, touched, smelt, and etc.

15
00:00:54,145 --> 00:00:56,979
or conceived of in the mind 
or intellectually.

16
00:00:56,979 --> 00:00:59,769
So then what are we doing?

17
00:01:00,046 --> 00:01:04,086
What is the Kṛṣṇa conscious project?

18
00:01:04,091 --> 00:01:08,403
We just said the whole talk 
up to this point was about this possibility,

19
00:01:08,403 --> 00:01:10,928
now we’re saying 
that it’s not possible

20
00:01:10,928 --> 00:01:13,893
with your senses, and your mind,
and your intellect.

21
00:01:13,893 --> 00:01:20,842
Well, what Śukadev said?
—“Beyond this realm,

22
00:01:20,842 --> 00:01:25,520
what I saw 
was not a mundane form,

23
00:01:25,520 --> 00:01:29,345
a mundane person, 
mundane relationship.

24
00:01:29,345 --> 00:01:32,464
That’s why every part of the Bhāgavatam
is significant.

25
00:01:32,464 --> 00:01:35,425
He was certified earlier,

26
00:01:35,425 --> 00:01:38,532
Remember, he is 
a sixteen-year-old boy, naked,

27
00:01:38,532 --> 00:01:46,042
wondering, when he goes pass a pound
where women are bathing naked.

28
00:01:46,043 --> 00:01:50,462
How would be average modern
sexteen-year-old boy responded that?

29
00:01:50,462 --> 00:01:53,226
—Let’s not go there.

30
00:01:53,226 --> 00:01:55,772
Śukadev Goswāmī …
They saw nothing—
 

31
00:01:55,772 --> 00:02:01,122
not even trace elements
of exploiting tendency in his vision.

32
00:02:01,672 --> 00:02:03,413
This is significant.

33
00:02:03,413 --> 00:02:06,945
So, he’s already been certified —
here is no interest,

34
00:02:06,945 --> 00:02:13,675
in a mundane … female form
or mundane sexuality.

35
00:02:13,866 --> 00:02:16,496
Then what does he hear about?

36
00:02:16,496 --> 00:02:19,906
—The erotic pastimes of Kṛṣṇa
and the Vraja-gopīs,

37
00:02:19,906 --> 00:02:23,302
and that captures
him wholesale.

38
00:02:23,302 --> 00:02:25,089
So, then what does it tell us?

39
00:02:25,089 --> 00:02:29,409
—There is erotic potential
in unalloyed devotion.

40
00:02:29,599 --> 00:02:32,324
Madan Mohan.

41
00:02:32,324 --> 00:02:36,419
Freud—
“Eros is driving the world.”

42
00:02:36,419 --> 00:02:43,710
The erotic principal is driving,
making the planet spin.

43
00:02:48,723 --> 00:02:52,336
Madan, Cupid, so

44
00:02:52,336 --> 00:02:56,846
sambandha-jñāna,
sambandha-tattva deity.

45
00:02:56,846 --> 00:03:03,036
Madan Mohan, we are all bewildered
by Cupid.

46
00:03:03,036 --> 00:03:06,912
Kṛṣṇa is so beautiful, 
Cupid becomes bewildered.

47
00:03:06,912 --> 00:03:09,960
And also it means that

48
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:20,330
the bewildering influence of Cupid
can be broken

49
00:03:20,330 --> 00:03:26,458
by becoming redirected
towards Madan Mohan Kṛṣṇa.

50
00:03:27,498 --> 00:03:32,719
Kṛṣṇa with erotic potential.
That’s what it means.

51
00:03:32,719 --> 00:03:44,061
So it’s very visual, very sensual—
the spiritual project.

52
00:03:44,077 --> 00:03:50,647
That requires a deeper level of seeing,
acquiring a proper angle of vision.

